@startuml
title Sequence Diagram: Authentication Flow (Register & Login)

actor User
participant "Client (CLI)" as Client
participant "Metadata Server\n(Master)" as Master

== 1. User Registration ==
User -> Client: Type 'adria register <user> <pass>'
activate Client
Client -> Master: Request Register (Username, Plain Password)
activate Master
Master -> Master: Check if Username exists
note right of Master: Security Rule:\nApply Cryptographic Hash\n(e.g., bcrypt) to password
Master -> Master: Save (Username, Hashed Password) to DB
Master --> Client: 201 Created (User registered)
deactivate Master
Client --> User: "Registration successful. Please login."
deactivate Client

== 2. User Login & Token Generation ==
User -> Client: Type 'adria login <user> <pass>'
activate Client
Client -> Master: Request Login (Username, Plain Password)
activate Master
Master -> Master: Fetch Hashed Password from DB
Master -> Master: Compare Hashes
note right of Master: If match, generate\nstateless JWT Token
Master --> Client: 200 OK (Auth Token)
deactivate Master

note over Client: Store Token locally\n(e.g., in memory or hidden config)
Client --> User: "Login successful. Session active."
deactivate Client

@enduml
